        <p data-uuid="1f32e143398544d48dc381a271ff087b">Abolitionist John Brown stunned the South when he attacked Harpers Ferry, Virginia, trying to start a slave rebellion. Many northerners called Brown a hero. The presidential election of 1860 took place in this bitter atmosphere. Republican <dfn title="Lincoln, Abraham">Abraham Lincoln</dfn> won the election without winning a single electoral vote from the South, upsetting southern leaders.</p>
